    "In fact, we can drop the assumption on a uniform profile and perform the convolution in Eq.",
    "(6) for different profile shapes.",
    "Therefore, if we know S(x, y; t, λ) from a standardised SN type and calculate F, then we can measure R(t).",
    "If the SN brightness profile shape varies over time, ratios of I (t, λ) can be considered for separations in time t small enough so that the profile does not change by much.",
